args: Hear ye, hear ye! Stand and recognize the\ncoming of the great kings of Balberia!
(I do hope Pia's idea goes well...)
Hmm? Hey! What's this on the table?!
I know that QUITE well just from looking\nat them! I am ASKING why there are\nfoodstuffs simply left out upon the table!
Your preparations are not even done yet!\nAre you having a laugh at me?!
Absolutely not, Your Half-Majesty!\nIn fact, let's do the final touches together!
Doesn't it seem a novel idea to choose\nyour own ingredients?
Perfect for a choosy king like yourself, no?
And I think you'll find that doing it together\nmakes everything even MORE fun!
Hrk! That pure smile of yours is so...\nso radiant!
Ugh. Well, it will be terrifically annoying\nif you start crying again, so...just one.
(Tsk! The food isn't even set out properly,\nyet they're still as excited as can be.\nHave they all taken leave of their wits?)
What's going to be different about\nmaking something myse... Hmm?
I just put the ingredients on the bread,\nso why is it THIS delicious?
Because we poured our hearts into it\nso you could have fun!
We didn't try to make it fancy because\nit was a tea party for royalty.
Instead, we thought about what you really\nwanted. That's what I meant.
Pouring your heart into something is\nan amazing thingâ€”and if you do it,\npeople are always able to tell.
That's why everything tastes so good!
I suppose this particular tea party does\nhave a rather...different cast to it.
Yep! And if you put your heart into it and\nconvey your feelings, you'll be able to\nmake all the friends you want!
How did you know about that?!
I knew it! You wanted a tea party you could\nhave with friends, didn't you?!
Is that specifically why you created\nthe unbirthday?
Oh, fine! Yes, you figured it out!\nIs that so bad?
You should have just said so instead of\ngetting angry and throwing people in jail.
How unseemly it would be for a monarch\nto desire friends! Read between the lines!\n...No, wait.
Your making me do the finishing touches\nwith you... Was that...?
Yeah, I thought it would be good to make\nthis feel like a real party with friends.
One where you participate in the fun\ninstead of having it all done for you.
So you weren't slacking off, but instead\npouring your heart into it?
Perhaps I should consider doing the\nsame thing myself.
I apologize for my actions, one and all!\nAnd though I am not deserving, might we\nenjoy a tea party together?
In that case, I'm going to free the people\nin jail, and then we can start the party!
Thank you for saving me, Pia.
And thank YOU for helping me before!
By way of apology for my past actions,\nI will grant all of you one single a wish.\nWhatever you like!
Just one? That's a little stingy...
I SAID they could wish for anything!
I think the answer is obvious.
No, don't grant my wish!\nGive everyone else something!
No. You did the lion's share of the work,\nand you should reap the reward.
It's because of you that we were able to\nhave this lovely tea party, after all.
In that case, I'd like to go back to my\nown world. Can you do that?
Of course! Crossing over a world or two\nis no trouble at all for one such as I!
If you keep sleeping outdoors,\nyou're going to catch cold.
Huh? Oh, Elias! Am I back?!
Back? What are you talking about?\nYou've been sleeping here in the courtyard.
Uh, has he EVER been able to?\nI think maybe you've been dreaming.
Was that really all just a dream?
Well, now that you're up, Cleo is looking\nfor someone to help with a tea party.\nYou should go check it out.
I might only be able to do small things,\nbut I've learned that pouring my heart into\nsomething is a task that even I can do!
And I'm going to use that talent to help\neveryone in the castle.
That sounds just like you, Pia.
Hee hee! Time for me to go out there\nand do my very best!
